# AGENTS.md

## Session Checklist

- Read `FRAMEWORK.md` once at the start of the session.
- Read the relevant spec in `specs/features/` before changing observable behavior.
- Read the relevant ADRs in `specs/decisions/` before changing areas governed by prior decisions.
- For any non-trivial change, recommend a workflow mode and ask the user how to proceed before implementing.
- Do not finish an observable behavior change without updating `specs/features/`.

## Context Hierarchy

- `FRAMEWORK.md` is the governing rule set.
- `specs/features/` is the canonical source of behavioral truth.
- `specs/decisions/` records governing architectural intent.
- This file is only the short operational entrypoint for future sessions.

Keep any extra project-specific instructions here so future sessions can recover context quickly without duplicating `FRAMEWORK.md`.

